{"name":"Back From The Dead","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character was dead, sort of. Maybe she got in over her head with the Triads or discovered information that was better left secret, and a megacorp took out a hit on her. Heck, maybe she was just in the wrong place at the wrong time. The streets are fickle that way. Cross the wrong group of people, turn down the wrong alley and it can end your life. Whatever the case, everyone thinks you are dead, and you like it that way. The rat bastards who took you out won’t ever see you coming.</p><p>Whenever your character confronts someone involved in your death, the NPC starts the encounter either Shaken if combat occurs, or she has a −2 to Social Conflicts if not in combat. This Edge doesn’t last forever, though. After your character has confronted everyone involved in your untimely demise, the Edge no longer provides its benefit. At that point in your story, you can choose a new Edge without having to spend an Advance. You must still meet the requirements to choose the Edge, though.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.q9fUzqk7nUumyF3E"},"cf":{"id":"temp_blbm6prf7","path":"Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"DBQPW55786KCBD3z"}
{"name":"Tannis Touch","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You hero is “attuned” to tannis. He can automatically identify where on the planet it came from, and if it’s a tool or weapon, gets a sense of any former owners, great deeds performed with the object, and so on.</p><p>The anouk can also merge tannis with other samples and shape it into simple tools or any of the anouk weapons listed in the Gear chapter. The stone slowly takes on the consistency of clay as he does so, then slowly hardens back to its natural hardness. This process takes an hour per pound of stone worked.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 39","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Anouk or Banshee Born or Guardian, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.ZtPoZDNeSuR8rvBo"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ozkdrtlws","path":"Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"E43er4ewFQL2JHLa"}
{"name":"Cyborg","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Cyborgs are humans (or other organic species) who have been augmented with mechanical parts. Sometimes this is done by choice; sometimes it’s the only way to save a badly wounded but still valuable asset.</p><p>The character’s Maximum Strain is doubled (see page 29). This does not stack with Cyber Tolerant, he may have one or the other. The individual must take an additional Major or two Minor Hindrances to compensate for this powerful Edge. Typically, this should relate to the story of how the hero became a cyborg.","notes":"Science Fiction Companion page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.science-fiction-companion.psqKksmYgCWNn3zG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_s841qkj1579","path":"Science Fiction Companion","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"FqszgknWhCLiyRGW"}
{"name":"Extra Effort","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Some Force Adepts can dig deep into their souls to significantly boost their powers.</p><p> Extra Effort increases a Force Use total after it’s rolled by +1 for 1 Power Point or +2 for 3 Power Points. It may not be used to improve a Critical Failure.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Force Adept), Force Use d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.JhIrh2j2IaqxoQ7g"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q446kdhr95l","path":"Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"HdcrNKq2jMdTEIcL"}
{"name":"Gun Fu Master!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This master of flowing pistol combat has evolved her techniques to compensate for motion. She may use the Marksman Edge while moving up to half Pace and may apply it to the first and second attacks she makes in a turn.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Enlightened Gun Fu!, Marksman"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.w9Mp4AplLDDXOuRq"},"cf":{"id":"temp_blbm6prf7","path":"Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"HpzZa8027pd30QlZ"}
{"name":"Guardian","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"On rare occasions, a colonist or anouk seemingly cheats death and returns to the land of the living. These lucky souls find themselves granted a second chance at life, but also return with a deep and profound connection to Banshee itself. This connection provides the Guardian with unique abilities, but also a responsibility to stand against the darkness that threatens to engulf the living planet. If your character is reborn into the life of a Guardian, you can read the details on it in No Man’s Land (page 69).</p><p>The Guardian Edge may only be selected at character creation, but you might become one if your hero bites the Banshee dust. See page 74 if you want to know more about becoming one of the living planet’s chosen protectors. Just realize it means taking a short dirt nap first...","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 39","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.x2zE5S0ffUmwwiDe"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ozkdrtlws","path":"Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"HytTpQzeGOOEJmFm"}
{"_id":"JZNTNPphx1wkDtsL","name":"Stinging Machines","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The machines are ready to react quickly when called upon by the mage. The mage ignores multi-action penalties when commanding the swarm (casting) and performing a Touch Attack to activate the Power. In other words, using the power and the touch attack would not incur the -2 penalty.","notes":"Nano-Mage Arcane Background, page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Nano-Mage, Novice, Master d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.nano-mage.JAEKCSzjkdtziAeI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_im5ud42srva","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Vulcan Nerve Pinch","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Make a touch attack called shot to your opponent’s vitals (cannot be a wild attack). Roll unarmed damage, but don’t apply it: instead, the victim must roll Vigor equal to the damage or immediately fall unconscious for 2d6 rounds. Does not affect energy beings, androids, Borg drones, or other creatures with a highly alien nervous system.","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice; Fighting d8; Knowledge (Biology) d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.x6xLpjfYCsg4hIPl"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5vc1mrusgz","path":"Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"KP40cF6kFYA1j6OG"}
{"name":"Survivalist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your rough upbringing has taught you how to survive on your own. You can ignore two points of penalties caused by an environmental condition (heat, cold, radiation, etc.).","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d6+, Survival: d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.jMKXNaZnvv9Xot56"},"cf":{"id":"temp_blbm6prf7","path":"Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"KZXlsDH8AN5OPWSf"}
{"name":"Guts","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This Way Out Wester isn’t fearless, she just bucks up and gets the job done even when she’s more scared than a long-tailed chanouk in a room full of rocking chairs.</p><p>Your hero gets a free reroll on Spirit rolls made to resist Fear.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 38","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.wTtyPY7pgbsdd5JN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ozkdrtlws","path":"Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"KcmmcUaJs7NJL2Pc"}
{"_id":"LgqXvPFWhV6vc0VG","name":"Arcane Background (Nano-Mage)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 2\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>&bull;Arcane Skill: Master (Smarts)</p>\n<p>&bull;Starting Powers: 3</p>\n<p>&bull;Power Points: 10</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div title=\"Page 2\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>The nanomachines have limited locomotion so they only have a range of touch or self. This decreases the power point cost by 1 as normal. For example, the caster desiring to cast Entangle on a foe would need to perform a successful touch attack.</p>\n<p>This limitation is offset by the ability to set a \"swarm trap\". The cost of the swarm trap is the same as the normal casting cost. A swarm trap is where part of a swarm lie in wait for something to come within its radius of affect. This is either the spell's normal effect or small blast template, whichever is larger. Spells that have a range can typically be used as a swarm trap.</p>\n<p>The caster stands at the center of the desired area of effect and casts the spell as normal. However, it does not go off immediately as the swarm simply stands in place waiting to be triggered. The swarm trap lasts as long as the caster stays within the range of the spell (for example, 2 x smarts for Blast) or dismissed. The caster may decide when the swarm triggers by setting a condition( for example, \"Someone enters the room\", \"Three bandits are by the tree\"). However, if the mage wishes to trigger the trap before the condition is met, the triggering uses the same rules as someone on Hold performing an Interrupting Action (Nano&shy;Mages also need to have Athletics to be successful). The mage's can recover invested Power Points when the trap triggers or when dispelled.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div title=\"Page 3\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><em>For example, A Mage wishes touse Blast to take out a rushing group of Bandits. The caster casts the Power where they stand. The cost is 2 Power Points (3 normally minus the 1 less Power Point cost for no range). The caster decides it is best to be careful and uses the Selective (+1 point for a total of 3 points) modifier to only affect the Bandits. The mage decides to trigger the trap when three bandits enter the blast radius of the Power. After casting, the Mage moves away 6 paces. Two Bandits stop to fire their pistols and another runs into the radius of the Blast Power. Since none of the bandits triggered the spell last round, the Mage decides to move another 4 paces and maintains the trap. Since he is within his Smarts X 2 (d10 Smarts) range of the Blast Power, the trap remains in effect. This round another bandit advanced into the blass area. The Mage decides to trigger the trap immediately instead of waiting for the condition to be met. The Mage rolls a 10 for Athletics check. The Bandits roll only a 5 and the swarm's Blast effect is triggered before the bandits can react. The Bandits take 2d6 damage! Now they know there is a Mage to contend with! </em></p>\n<p>A swarm trap cannot be noticed or detected under normal circumstances (the GM may decide if Detect Arcana will discover traps). The trap also cannot activate until the mage moves away from it (they cannot get around the touch requirement by casting a trap and then triggering immediately) .</p>\n<p><strong>Source:&nbsp;</strong>Nano-Mage Arcane Background, page 2</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div title=\"Page 2\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.2pQIprovBCT0uiKt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_im5ud42srva","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Bio Hunter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Bio Hunters destroy the biological horrors (biohorrors) that infest numerous areas, either by accident or intent. As a cleaner, you deal with all manner of strange creatures on a daily basis. To successfully combat these creatures, you need to have a broad understanding of their biology and iron nerves. A cleaner can Reroll Fear checks. Extensive research also allows the cleaner to exploit weak points, increasing the bonus damage from Called Shots by +2; this only affects Called Shots that already get bonus damage.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 44","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d6+, Research d6+, Shooting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.uVhmPwgkTefBj93x"},"cf":{"id":"temp_blbm6prf7","path":"Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Ljoph3klC8Mi3hxK"}
{"name":"Miracle Worker","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"People don’t die on your watch. You won’t let them. Call it strength of will, exceptional skill, or just plain stubbornness, but you have a knack for resuscitating the dead. You can revive a person who has died by making a Healing roll at a −1 penalty for every minute that has passed since the character died (max 5 minutes). Each attempt takes a minute.</p><p>Characters that are revived are considered to be Stable (and have three Wounds) but have three levels of Fatigue (as per Savage Worlds core rules) that recovers one level per day. A raise removes one level of Fatigue.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d10+, Healing d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.mmOjztBUSXZs0Yl1"},"cf":{"id":"temp_blbm6prf7","path":"Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"LzRNFvp1LcRZtr7x"}
{"name":"Mentalist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Constant contact with multiple minds gives this Force User an edge when it comes to forcing or resisting Force assaults. They may add a +2 to opposed Force rolls, whether they are using their powers against a foe or defending against a rival.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any), Smarts d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.ZdkZVaVjHBLijgUj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q446kdhr95l","path":"Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"MKRR5PngMd5EljXc"}
{"name":"Analyze Shield Harmonics","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your understanding of electromagnetism lets you find weak spots that others don't even know to look for. You may scan an opponent’s shield frequency mid-battle by making a Knowledge (Astronomy) roll. With a success, your vessel’s energy weapons gain +4 AP against that vessel. This lasts until an officer aboard the target ship realigns their shields with a Knowledge (Starship Operations) check, at –2 if you got a raise.","notes":"Star Trek page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice. Knowledge (Astronomy) d6; Knowledge (Starship Operations) d6."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.rnpSnP9EiJFGQlYV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5vc1mrusgz","path":"Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"MLTTqxFfqhquU4XQ"}
{"name":"Strategema Master","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The Zackdorn game of strategema can be mastered only by those with a split-second ability to assess a tactical situation and eke out every advantage. You gain +2 to all Gambling checks, as well as to Knowledge (Tactics) checks when leading one side during a Mass Battle.","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; Knowledge (Tactics) d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.1uoUEgefezNb4uTK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5vc1mrusgz","path":"Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"NgdYCBpnCOgSfb8A"}
{"name":"Gravitic Acclimation","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your spacer knows how to operate in different gravities. She ignores the usual −2 penalty for operating in a gravity other than her own (see Zero-G, page 64).","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 38","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.wO22VmjWnBnQCTYG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ozkdrtlws","path":"Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QCZYLnIENYyCrNgi"}
