{"name":"Starfleet Commander","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your training, experience, and instincts have paid off: under your command, your ship is a well-functioning machine that proudly goes where no one has gone before. Crews who serve you add +2 to their Knowledge (Starship Operations), Knowledge (Engineering), Piloting, Tracking, and Stealth rolls while aboardship. Does not apply to the ship’s AI.","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; Smarts d8; Knowledge (Starship Operations) d8; Diplomacy or Intimidation d8; Command; must be sole captain of the vessel"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.tbXZlJbDn7mc85fY"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5vc1mrusgz","path":"Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"dNjLtx3i6sYtAC4P"}
{"name":"Reputation","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character managed to impress the masses with his ability to get things done. His Street Cred die type is increased by 1 to a max of d12+2. This Edge may be taken up to three times. The Edge may only be taken a second time when the character is Veteran or a third when he reaches Legendary.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.tE6cxbvGxAFtW4lB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_blbm6prf7","path":"Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"dTBN3UOehPPTJzG0"}
{"name":"Evasive Maneuvers","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The enemy ship is firing everything she’s got, but nothing seems to land as you loop, scissor, and roll out of the way. As long as you are piloting the ship, enemies subtract 1 from their Shooting rolls to hit (also applies to torpedo locks). Additionally, if you choose to flee combat, the length of the Chase is reduced by one round (typically from 3 to 2, but it’s the GM’s discretion).","notes":"Star Trek page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; Piloting d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.TT9OD1MG1Suw7hbB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5vc1mrusgz","path":"Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"dtX65DDhuRI0Tfee"}
{"name":"Gun Fu!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Heavily trained in close quarters gunplay, you know gun fu. When using pistols against a target’s Parry, she has +2 to Shooting and +2 to pistol damage. This benefit only applies to such close range combat, not to attacks from further than adjacent.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Martial Artist, Fighting d6+, Shooting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.6clDV7NZJYo0uhXo"},"cf":{"id":"temp_blbm6prf7","path":"Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ec57W8SI6bwXdl5Z"}
{"name":"Adapted","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Not all anouks shun technology. This Edge removes the Low Tech racial Hindrance from an anouk hero so she can operate most human technology normally.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 36","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Anouk, Novice, Smarts d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.mcTLpjluHzXTMflI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ozkdrtlws","path":"Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"enDWteeIkEwNQoqA"}
{"name":"Alternate Identity","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You have another identity you are known by, airtight with background, job history, computer records, official documentations, etc. This lets you operate under an alias that cannot easily be traced back to you, since everything checks out for all but the most persistent snoop. If the character’s identity is ever revealed through his actions (or inactions), he loses the benefits of this Edge. This Edge may be taken multiple times, each time the Edge is taken the character gains a new identity.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.7B9Svgfu0j0wD7Si"},"cf":{"id":"temp_blbm6prf7","path":"Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"fCfPVSY3sQfjsVIg"}
{"name":"Fire At Will","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Subtlety and precision are all well and good, but sometimes what you need is to lock and fire as many photon torpedoes as you possibly can in less than ten seconds. You may fire one weapon system per round without incurring a multi-action penalty.","notes":"Star Trek page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice; Shooting d6; Knowledge (Starship Operations) d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.Ld09bWAkaekOErLy"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5vc1mrusgz","path":"Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"fqMDka64hzvtr7nG"}
{"name":"Geared Up","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This Edge may only be taken at character creation. Your character has up to $10,000 worth of possessions each time this Edge is taken. This is a one-time only benefit—if the gear is lost, it’s lost","notes":"Science Fiction Companion page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.science-fiction-companion.3mTIJr2EOrHJYCHk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_s841qkj1579","path":"Science Fiction Companion","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"ftlp8DBvXrtx6Fzp"}
{"name":"Xenodiplomat","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You may ignore up to 4 penalty points to your Charisma when acting as the main point of contact to an alien species.","notes":"Star Trek page 9","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice; Knowledge (Xenocultures) d6; Diplomacy d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.bZ6nv4jlxeuUX2Xr"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5vc1mrusgz","path":"Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"gUXdrU5mzL9DLFJS"}
