{"_id":"jWt236RNL5duvrc7","name":"Arcane Background (Telepathy)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-size: 16px;\">Arcane Skill: Telepathy (Smarts)</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-size: 16px;\">Starting&nbsp;<a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-color: initial; padding: initial; white-space: initial; word-break: initial; margin: initial; color: var(--red); text-decoration-line: underline; border: initial initial initial;\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"swade-core-rules.swade-rules\" data-id=\"WaqU65ZxvBkQ0pKc\">Powers</a>: 2</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-size: 16px;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-color: initial; padding: initial; white-space: initial; word-break: initial; margin: initial; color: var(--red); text-decoration-line: underline; border: initial initial initial;\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"swade-core-rules.swade-rules\" data-id=\"I3euc03IC9TAW83S\">Power Points</a>: 10</li>\n</ul>\n<p>There are many telepathic races in Star Trek, such as Vulcans and Betazoids. Players of those races may take the Arcane Background (Telepathy) edge, which works exactly as Arcane Background (Psionics) in Savage Worlds, except that telepaths' available powers are limited to...</p>\n<p><em>Blind, confusion, disguise, fear, invisibility, puppet, mind reading, slow, slumber, and speak language.</em></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.mfAVN2iGJ81Ybtcc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_im5ud42srva","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Improved Evasive Maneuvers","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"As Evasive Maneuvers, but attackers subtract 2 from their attack rolls, and when you flee combat the length of the Chase is reduced by 2 rounds.","notes":"Star Trek page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran; Evasive Maneuvers"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.OYOIyHXfwAj5YXs3"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5vc1mrusgz","path":"Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"jtooUs1xFVq05tHn"}
{"name":"Artificer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Those who use the Force sometimes find ways to imbue powers into items. They may turn an ordinary blade into a “Magic” sword, grant powerful potions to their friends, or even create powerful relics with imbued power.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.LgWBmhk15bGWcpSj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q446kdhr95l","path":"Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"kCaCsT3rAgAyiXr8"}
{"name":"Sector Cop","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Sector cops blend training and experience in getting instant compliance from anyone that hears them use ‘cop voice’. This Edge has three effects.</p><p>First, a Critical Failure never makes the target immune to this Sector Cop’s Intimidation. Second, a success on the opposed roll when using Intimidation out of combat works like a raise; the target backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills their guts, or flees with all haste depending on the situation. Third, a success when using Taunt out of combat works like a raise; the victim is cowed for the scene, departs obviously distraught, or attacks recklessly at the GM’s discretion.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Spirit d6+, Intimidation d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.moGd3vU36ICbIcsc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_blbm6prf7","path":"Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"khZhLServO6NVvH2"}
