{"name":"Street Samurai","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Street Samurai are mercenaries with hearts of gold (not literally; golden hearts are heavy and inefficient). They aren’t as common as fiction claims, but they are trustworthy. A samurai starts with Street Cred d8 and gets a free Reroll on failures when using Street Cred.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 45","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Code of Honor or Heroic"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.eLRSaMoavk0JmDUj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_blbm6prf7","path":"Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"lbJdWuAjoHQfOqcV"}
{"name":"Jedi/Sith Warrior","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Jedi/Sith face grave danger in service to the Force. To survive such hardships, they learn to channel the Force to protect themselves. They may add +1 to total of a final Soak roll for each Power Point spent, to a maximum of +4.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Jedi/Sith), Force Use d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.TLl2IwcYIrFcjs1E"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q446kdhr95l","path":"Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"otJinBTyu3np2O7x"}
{"name":"Reroute Auxiliary Power","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When rerouting power, you trade energy “at cost” rather than at one-half. For example, draining 8 Shields can energize the Targeting Computers by +2, instead of +1. In other words, a Half-Step is traded for a Half-Step, and a Full-Step is traded for a Full-Step. (See ‘Reroute Power’ in Setting Rules for more information.)","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran; Knowledge (Starship Operations) d8; Knowledge (Engineering) d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.uIWKXEIlCnAsjoPR"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5vc1mrusgz","path":"Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"pabDuoGraoMVYULo"}
{"name":"Jedi Knight/Sith Knight","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"While you have a Lightsaber readied and you are aware of a ranged attack, the Target Number for the attacker equals your Parry score. This does not apply to area attacks.</p><p> You may throw your Lightsaber as a Multi-action in a straight line a number of inches equal to half your Force Use die and then recall your saber back to your hand. Making one Melee attack against a single target that you can see anywhere along the way. This takes all three of your actions. (one to throw it, one to attack, one to call it back) This attack does not suffer from MAP.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Force Sensitive (Jedi/Sith), Trademark Weapon (Lightsaber)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.GLG1bp4qWZ9mH2aE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q446kdhr95l","path":"Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"pgzSRi68DVJ7a0iv"}
{"name":"Hacker","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"As a hacker, you are committed to learning everything you can about the science (or art) of cracking into secure systems. Your skills give you an edge in many situations, whether you are using your TAP to shut down an opponent’s Cybertech, or when you use a hacking rig to invade corporate mainframes.</p><p>You gain the use of programs and begin play with two programs of your choice. You must meet the requirements to use the program, however. Hacking is the skill you use to launch your programs. You may obtain more programs by choosing the “New Power” Edge. Finally, If using the Bring the Pain plugin (page 120), you get +1 Toughness to resist Intrusion Countermeasures.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 44","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6, Hacking d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.8072qF9MkIoWlvxL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_blbm6prf7","path":"Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"pqbWLCOycOOd4qug"}
{"name":"True Grit","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This grizzled spacer has seen some things that’d make others’ eyes pop like they were decompressing. He ignores all penalties when making Fear checks, and if failed, gets one free reroll on the Fear Effects table if he chooses.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 39","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Grit, Spirit d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.EPAUngMAGXKLLhkd"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ozkdrtlws","path":"Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"rIukqIESlAW1bx3u"}
{"name":"Cyber Tolerant","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The individual’s body can handle cyberware better than most. His Maximum Strain for cyberware is increased by +4 (see page 29).","notes":"Science Fiction Companion page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.science-fiction-companion.cesROih53hfEhiTg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_s841qkj1579","path":"Science Fiction Companion","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"rTYg069wiBL1BSNS"}
{"name":"Quick Draw","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You draw two additional cards when spending a Benny for an Action Card at the beginning of a round instead of one. You may choose your final Action Card from any of your available choices, including additional draws from Level Headed, Quick, etc.</p><p>You also add +2 to Athletics rolls made to interrupt others’ actions (including resisting being interrupted).","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 37","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.pn0u7KhFTCYzY3CT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ozkdrtlws","path":"Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"rpaxtS5jlA8SqZMe"}
{"name":"Don’t Get ’im Riled!","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Heroes with this Edge are a mean and surly lot. They add their current Wounds to any Fighting damage rolls, to a maximum of +3.</p><p>A hero with three Wounds, for example, adds +3 to his melee damage. It has no effect on ranged or thrown attacks.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 37","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.p0VzDVKA0kauvh47"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ozkdrtlws","path":"Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"t9mRca53fxNYXShV"}
{"name":"Mandalorian","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Mandalorians are trained from a Young age to be ready for combat at any time. They get a +1 on all Fighting and Shooting Rolls. They also receive a +1 to any Piloting Roll made to use a Jetpack.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Soldier"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.0nGFgm0SxqMYhkXk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q446kdhr95l","path":"Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"tAZ1Xd3urVZEdM5U"}
{"name":"Pack Fighting","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"You have a natural talent for turning overwhelming force into overwhelming damage. You add half your gang-up bonus (round down) to damage for melee attacks.","notes":"Interface Zero 3.0 Players Guide page 43","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.interface-zero-30.CsEWO3F0gty8WlYG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_blbm6prf7","path":"Interface Zero 3.0","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"tYWD1Ym9SOwtkC2q"}
{"_id":"uoyUNkRCbDeE3K42","name":"Fast Machines","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The machines have become faster and can move more quickly. The mage can use a power at the normal range defined in the Power's description by expending +2 Power Points. ","notes":"Nano-Mage Arcane Background, page 4","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Nano-Mage, Veteran, Master d10 "}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.nano-mage.jLtEVGauQulOzYSG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_im5ud42srva","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Heavy-G Worlder","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The character comes from a dense world with very heavy gravity. He starts with a d6 in Strength, doubles normal jumping distances, adds +2 to his Pace, his running die increases one step, and does not suffer the –2 Agility penalty for Normal gravity.</p><p>The character must take an additional Major Hindrance or two Minor Hindrances to balance out this particularly powerful Edge.","notes":"Science Fiction Companion page 12","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.science-fiction-companion.BTwOwkZepUXHLg4H"},"cf":{"id":"temp_s841qkj1579","path":"Science Fiction Companion","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"v6OLIrlrJl7aNI3e"}
{"name":"Colonial Ranger","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Colonial Rangers are the law enforcement arm of the United Colonial Assembly, a body currently led by former corporate shill turned people's champion JJ Lasster.</p><p>Officially , the Rangers’ jurisdiction only encompasses Banshee and any vessel or station in orbit around it. Since Operation Typhon and colonial revolt against EXFOR, the Rangers have carefully extended their reach further into space.</p><p>Most settlements on Banshee have Town Marshals, with the Rangers acting as traveling supervisors and judges. Space colonies have a Station Marshal that fulfills the same purpose. (EXFOR ships and HI-dedicated stations furnish their own security.)</p><p>The Rangers tend to stay out of system politics, however, leaving that to the Colonial Assembly and Chairman JJ Lasseter's capable mind. Most of the law dogs' time is spent keeping humans and anouks from killing each other, a constant and thankless task.</p><p>Colonial Rangers receive the title and badge but actual authority comes as it always does—with attitude, willpower, and occasional violence.</p><p>Rangers also get a uniform (which few wear), a Dragoon pistol with two full loads of ammo, their choice of six mini-grenades (see page 47), and body armor (page 45). Basic equipment damaged in the course of duty can be replaced free of charge at any Ranger station (found in most settlements over a few hundred).</p><p>Mission-essential equipment, such as a Stallion (page 60) or other vehicle, may be assigned by the hero’s superior officers on as-needed basis.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 38","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d6+, Common Knowledge d6+, Language (Anouk) d4+, Intimidation d6+, Shooting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.3YtccYjLxbB1mjHM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ozkdrtlws","path":"Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"vsdnAOp0PFKchqSl"}
{"_id":"wHhb654yyqTNaqV3","name":"Infused Machines","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"The mage is so connected with the machines that he can leverage them for soak rolls. Each PP provides a +1 to Soak Rolls to a maximum of +4.","notes":"Nano-Mage Arcane Background, page 3","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Nano-Mage, Seasoned, Master d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.nano-mage.7cISEWIOMncYQMpU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_im5ud42srva","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Banshee Born","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your character is a human born and raised on Banshee. The living planet connected with her on a spiritual level, allowing her to take any Edge or ability usually reserved only for anouks. Furthermore, when her time comes, she’s more likely to become a Guardian (see Guardians on page 74).</p><p>Some Banshee Born have the Outsider Hindrance, but it’s not mandatory . Occasional colonists may see her as having “gone native,” and the most ignorant and racist of the lot may occasionally use this as an excuse for violence, but most don’t know or care.</p><p> Anouks are slightly more favorable to Banshee Born humans—add +1 to Persuasion rolls with dealing with them.","notes":"Deadlands Lost Colony page 37","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Human"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.deadlands-lost-colony.PemEzycYIRLDbTEM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ozkdrtlws","path":"Deadlands: Lost Colony","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"wYO1NPfQtGECoUwW"}
{"name":"Hack Sensors","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"A crafty officer may attempt to hack opponents’ sensors and upload false readings. To do so, roll Knowledge (Computers) opposed by whomever is manning the opponent's sensors. With a success, the opponent's sensors (including targeting) suffer a –1 penalty as you fill their readout with ‘white noise’. The victim can fix the hack with a Repair roll, at –2 if you scored a raise.","notes":"Star Trek page 7","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; Knowledge (Computers) d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.ks9O88UiSJ928wKM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5vc1mrusgz","path":"Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"wZh3kQd8LIFOxsUL"}
{"name":"Coordinated Firing","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This edge allows the character to benefit from gang up bonus when making ranged attacks in coordination with anyone else who also has this edge. When both characters are attacking the same declared target that round. They must make this declaration before either one acts that round. The max benefit from this is +4.","notes":"Savage Star Wars page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shooting d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-wars.zn28o0e1toKOqoM6"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q446kdhr95l","path":"Star Wars","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"xiPYeClNjCojmjgn"}
{"name":"Improved Hack Sensors","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"As Hack Sensors, but you may also create a false image of another ship, up to one Size larger than your own (a sudden reinforcement, a mutual enemy, even a mirror image of your own vessel). The phantom is dispersed when the computer hack is fixed.","notes":"Star Trek page 8","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran; Hack Sensors"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.star-trek.8OxuvGWrRsgZg8xI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5vc1mrusgz","path":"Star Trek","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"xnoJneB8NmQcISkA"}
